sentences: Natalia Lvovna "Natasha" Vlassenko (Russian: Ната́лья Льво́вна Вла́сенко; born 20 November 1956) is a Russian-Australian pianist and teacher.
In 1977, she won third prize at the International Beethoven Competition in Vienna.
In 1985, she went on to win third prize at the Ferruccio Busoni International Piano Competition in Bolzano, Italy.
In 1999, Vlassenko and her husband Oleg Stepanov co-founded the Lev Vlassenko Piano Competition in memory of her father Lev Vlassenko.
The competition is the only major piano event in Australia that mirrors the requirements of an international competition and is held in Brisbane every two years since 1999.
